summary_markdown: This data presents a comparative analysis of two types of urban centers based on their communication infrastructure and associated costs. "High-speed letter cities" represent 27% of the analyzed urban areas, indicating a significant portion of cities with advanced, likely digital, communication capabilities. In contrast, "Low-cost Telegram cities" constitute 23%, suggesting a segment of cities that rely on or are characterized by more traditional, potentially less expensive, communication methods. The structure is a simple comparison of two distinct categories of cities, highlighting their relative prevalence within an unspecified dataset.
